==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Droil
<hw>Droil</hw> <pr>(droil)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>druilen</ets> to mope.]</ety> <def>To work sluggishly or slowly; to
plod.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Droil</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Droil
<hw>Droil</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>druil</ets> sluggard. Cf.
<er>Droll</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A drudge.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Beau. & Fl.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Mean labor; toil.</def><mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Droit</ent>⟦br⟧
